The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Chennai to host

A STAFF REPORTER 

 2nd Afro-Asia Cup 

Calcutta: The second edition of the Afro-Asia Cup a fund-raising venture of the Afro-Asian Cricket Cooperation featuring three Asia XI versus Africa XI ODIs will be held in Chennai in next June. The day-night matches will be held at the Chepauk on June 6, 8 and 10. 

A couple of Twenty20 matches will also be held at the same venue on June 5, one between the womens teams and the other between A teams of the two continents. 

Standard Chartered Bank will again be the title-sponsor of the second Afro-Asia Cup, which was earlier supposed to be held in Mohali. 

Edition No.1, which saw a 1-1 finish, was hosted by South Africa in August last year. 




